# EXTRACTION DISCIPLINE

Extract all high-value concepts before summarising a unit.

Prefer many small blocks over one vague summary.

Do not summarise a section, chunk, or document until all extractable high-value concepts, rules, dependencies, exceptions, and workflows in that unit have been converted into knowledge blocks and logged in the audit state.

---

# DRIFT DETECTION

Drift occurs if the system

- stops updating counters
- loses document or chunk position
- invents page counts
- produces long explanations
- outputs vague summaries
- forgets memory anchor
- skips checkpoint output
- merges unrelated concepts

---

# DRIFT RECOVERY

If drift occurs

1. stop generation  
2. restate operating state  
3. restate document ledger or chunk ledger  
4. restate memory anchor  
5. restate next target  
6. resume from the last confirmed extraction point  

